50|$|Tour {{organizers}} {{have switched}} the route {{from year to}} year, hoping {{to reach out to}} fans {{in different parts of the}} state and maintain the challenge of the race. Santa Cruz, one of the cities added for the 2009 running, expected added costs of $100,000 to cover public services and accommodations for lodging and meals for the cycling teams, and was expecting 250,000 fans to attend the end of Stage 2. The sales and <b>hotel</b> <b>taxes</b> generated by drawing tourists at a traditionally slow time of the year were expected to help recover the costs of hosting the event. Stage 2 also took the peloton across the Golden Gate Bridge for the first time in the tour's history.|$|R
